Package org.neo4j.internal.batchimport.cache.idmapping.string

Class Workers<R extends Runnable>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.neo4j.internal.batchimport.cache.idmapping.string.Workers<R>
  • Type Parameters:
    R - type of workers
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<R>
    public class Workers<R extends Runnable>
extends Object
implements Iterable<R>
    Utility for running a handful of Runnable in parallel, each in its own thread. Runnable instances are added and started and the caller can await() them all to finish, returning a error if any thread encountered one so that the caller can decide how to handle that error. Or caller can use awaitAndThrowOnError() where error from any worker would be thrown from that method. It's basically like using an ExecutorService, but without that "baggage" and an easier usage and less code in the scenario described above.
